gomodel:SYNGO_2537  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From Results section:\n\nThe 1.0/1.3 M sucrose interface consists primarily of synaptic plasma membranes with a portion of their postsynaptic membrane and postsynaptic density attached. (...) Using the anti-14-3-3 antiserum as a probe, the immunoreactivity was most concentrated in the M1.0 and synaptic plasma membrane fractions.\n\nTo characterise further the location of the 14-3-3 in the synaptic membrane preparation, the iodonitrotetrazolium-treated membranes were extracted with 0.2% Triton X-100, and the Triton-soluble and -insoluble components were separated by centrifugation through a layer of 1 M sucrose. (...) The ß/ζ isoforms appeared to be quantitatively solubilised by the treatment, whereas the isoforms γ, ε, and η were present in each of the three fractions at similar concentrations . This suggests that some of the γ, ε, and η isoforms may be associated with postsynaptic densities.. Experimental description: From methods section:\nBrains from adult Sprague-Dawley rats were subfractionated according to a slight modification of the method of Weinberger and Rostas (1986)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2537" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

